ddateien sind lizenziert als&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.de\" target=\"_blank\">Public Domain Mark 1.0<\/a>. Berlin, M\u00fcnzkabinett der Staatlichen Museen, 18318700. Aufnahme durch Christian Stoess.","en":"Image files are licensed&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.en\" target=\"_blank\">Public Domain Mark 1.0<\/a>. Berlin, M\u00fcnzkabinett der Staatlichen Museen, 18318700. Photographs by Christian Stoess."}},"division":{"ikmk_division_id":"2","division_name_de":"Mittelalter","division_name_en":"Medieval Period"},"sub_division":{"ikmk_subdivision_id":"17","subdivision_name_de":"Fr\u00fchmittelalter","subdivision_name_en":"Early Middle Ages"},"literatur":"B. Kluge, State Museum Berlin Coin Cabinet. Anglo-Saxon, Anglo-Norman, and Hiberno Norse Coins. Sylloge of Coins of the British Isles 36 (1987) Nr. 32 (dieses St\u00fcck); J. J. North, English Hammered Coinage I \u00b3(1994) Nr. 116; T. Abramson, Sceattas. An illustrated guide (2006) 74 Nr. X120; C. Feveile, Series X and Coin Circulation in Ribe, in: T. Abramson (Hrsg.), Studies in Early Medieval Coinage 1. Two Decades of Discovery (2008) 53-67 (ab 705-725); A. Gannon, British Museum. Anglo-Saxon Coins I. Early Anglo-Saxon Gold and Anglo-Saxon and Continental Silver Coinage of the North Sea Area, c. 600-760. Sylloge of Coins of the British Isles 63 (2013) Nr. 446-451 (710-760); T. Abramson, The Abramson Collection. Coins of Early Anglo-Saxon England and the North Sea Area. Sylloge of Coins of the British isles 69 (2016) 334-341; T. Abramson, Scaetta List (2017) 327 ff. Nr. 103-10 (710-800); Coins of England & the United Kingdom. Pre-Decimal Issues (2019) Nr. 797.","comment":"Dieser sog. Typ 'Wodan\/Monster' wird in der englischen Numismatik als Serie X oder Typ 31 zu den 'Continental Sceattas' gerechnet. Als Ursprung wird auch D\u00e4nemark (Ribe) vermutet. Vgl. M. Metcalf, Thrymsas and Sceattas in the Ashmolean Museum Oxford II (1993) 275-293 und Nr. 275-281. Es handelt sich um eine zeitgen\u00f6ssische Kupferf\u00e4lschung der Silberm\u00fcnze.","period":{"ikmk_period_id":"11","name_de":"Fr\u00fchmittelalter","name_en":"Early Middle ages","description_de":"Bezeichnung f\u00fcr die Epoche von ungef\u00e4hr 500 bis ca. 900 (teilweise auch um 1000).","description_en":"Term to describe the period between c. 500 and c. 900 (in some regions to c. 1000).","concept_id":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/7503821-3","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/period\/11"},"year_start":"710","year_end":"750","date_verbal":"710-750","year_islam":"0","manufacturing":[{"ikmk_manufacturing_id":"21","manufacturing_name_de":"gepr\u00e4gt","manufacturing_name_en":"struck","nomisma_id":"http:\/\/nomisma.org\/id\/struck","ndp_uri":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/manufacture\/21"}],"linked_persons_corporations":{"50":{"ikmk_type_id":"50","type_name_de":"Vorbesitzer","type_name_en":"previous Owner","type_nomisma_id":"","type_concept_id":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4447273-0","ndp_id":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/type_for_person_and_corporation\/50","items":{"6118":{"ikmk_person_id":"6118","title_de":"Generalmajor","first_name_de":"August","last_name_de":"R\u00fchle von Lilienstern","vitalDates":"16.04.1780 - 01.07.1847","title_en":"Major general","first_name_en":"August","last_name_en":"R\u00fchle von Lilienstern","corporation":"0","lod":{"https:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/116675799":"https:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/116675799","https:\/\/viaf.org\/viaf\/27828907":"https:\/\/viaf.org\/viaf\/27828907","https:\/\/www.wikidata.org\/wiki\/Q74040":"https:\/\/www.wikidata.org\/wiki\/Q74040","https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/6118":"https:\/\/ikmk.smb.museum\/ndp\/person\/6118"},"year_from":"0","year_until":"1842"}}}},"keywords":[{"ikmk_keyword_id":"71","keyword_de":"Bronze \/ Kupfer","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4146667-6","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/www.nomisma.org\/id\/ae"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"75","keyword_de":"Fabelwesen","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4016114-6","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300379738"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"81","keyword_de":"F\u00e4lschungen","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4016247-3","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300015641"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"8","keyword_de":"Fr\u00fchmittelalter, 5.-9. Jh.","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/7503821-3","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300020760"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"45","keyword_de":"G\u00f6tter","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4021469-2","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300343850"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"2","keyword_de":"Mittelalter","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4129108-6","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/aat\/300020756"},{"ikmk_keyword_id":"21","keyword_de":"Nordeuropa","keyword_gnd_uri":"http:\/\/d-nb.info\/gnd\/4075455-8","keyword_concept_uri":"http:\/\/vocab.getty.edu\/tgn\/4003757"}],"timeline_themes":[{"ikmk_timeline_id":"137","timeline_item":"Angelsachsen und Friesen - Die Sceattas","description":"Eine Besonderheit des Fr\u00fchmittelalters bilden die kleinen dicken Silberm\u00fcnzen der Angelsachsen und Friesen, die sog. Sceattas. Bei der Namensgebung stand die in einem Gesetz K\u00f6nig Ethelberts von Kent (601-604) verwendete Bezeichnung sceat Pate, die eigentlich keine spezifischen M\u00fcnze, sondern allgemein Silbergeld meint und als Schatz bzw. Schatzgeld zu \u00fcbersetzen ist. Die genaueren Zuschreibungen der Sceattas sind problematisch, weil sie daf\u00fcr wegen ihrer Schriftlosigkeit und schwer zu deutenden Bilder kaum brauchbare Anhaltspunkte bieten. Sie sind von ca. 680 bis um 750 beiderseits des Kanals in England und in Friesland, m\u00f6glicherweise auch in Skandinavien gepr\u00e4gt worden. Angels\u00e4chsische und kontinentale Anteile dieser durch eine gleichartige Technik gekennzeichneten M\u00fcnzgruppe lassen sich nur schwer trennen. Als friesisch gelten die sog. Porcupine (=Stachelschwein)-Typen.","year_from":"680","year_until":"765","autor":"Kluge, Bernd"}],"text_right":{"short":"CC BY-SA 4.0","icon":"https:\/\/licensebuttons.net\/l\/by-sa\/4.0\/80x15.png","url":{"de":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-sa\/4.0\/deed.de","en":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-sa\/4.0\/deed.en"},"label":{"de":"Creative Commons Namensnennung - Weitergabe unter gleichen Bedingungen 4.0 International","en":"Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International"},"string":{"de":"Texte und Beschreibungen in diesem Online-Katalog stehen unter einer\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-sa\/4.0\/deed.de\" target=\"_blank\">CC BY-SA 4.0<\/a> Lizenz.","en":"Texts and descriptions of this catalogue are licensed <a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-sa\/4.0\/deed.en\" target=\"_blank\">CC BY-SA 4.0<\/a>."}},"lod_right":{"short":"PDM 1.0","icon":"https:\/\/licensebuttons.net\/p\/zero\/1.0\/80x15.png","url":{"de":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.de","en":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.en"},"label":{"de":"Public Domain Mark 1.0","en":"Public Domain Mark 1.0"},"string":{"de":"Verwendete LOD-Identifikatoren sind <a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.de\" target=\"_blank\">Public Domain Mark 1.0<\/a>\u00a0lizenziert.","en":"LOD ids used are licensed <a href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.en\" target=\"_blank\">Public Domain Mark 1.0<\/a>."}},"image_restriction_id":0,"image_restriction":"free","image_right":{"short":"PDM 1.0","icon":"https:\/\/licensebuttons.net\/p\/zero\/1.0\/80x15.png","url":{"de":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.de","en":"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/publicdomain\/mark\/1.0\/deed.en"},"label":{"de":"Public Domain Mark 1.0","en":"Public Domain Mark 1.0"}}}